11/06/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Bucharest opens a conference Friday (11 June) on the EU accession process for Southeast European states. Romania's deputy chief negotiator with the EU, Leonard Orban, will attend. Participants will discuss the experiences of Bulgaria, Croatia, Hungary, Romania and Slovenia.
In other news, Romania on Wednesday was appointed chairman of the UN Security Council Committee 1540 on non-proliferation of weapons of mass destruction by non-state actors. The foreign ministry says the appointment represents recognition of the country's conduct in the field of non-proliferation and proves its capacity to build consensus within the Security Council. (Rompres - 11/06/04)
